OL,7,FMr Perks had thought the intruder was
OL,8,Fhis son because he had the same "big,
OL,9,Fsolid" build.
OL,11,FJurors were told Mr Perks was blinded
OL,12,Fby the head torch of a man he thought
OL,13,Fwas wearing a balaclava before being
OL,14,Fstabbed in the abdomen, leaving him in
OL,15,Fintensive care.
OL,17,FHe said he could not see the
OL,18,Fintruder's face because they had a
OL,19,Fheadlight on and he thought they might
OL,20,Fbe wearing a balaclava.
